cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.MM

This paper discusses the analysis of trends on a Chinese microblogging social network, which falls under the category of social media analysis. Therefore, cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the analysis of media content such as images and videos, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of text data, which could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
